A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Reinsurance for Essential Industries; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, continual increases in both the frequency and severity of claims will increase
4 the cost of the property and casualty reinsurance market, which results in higher premiums
5 and lower coverage; and
6 WHEREAS, commercial property and casualty insurance brokers have reported quarterly
7 price increases of an average of six percent ,which can pressure insured entities to purchase
8 inadequate products that do not reflect their actual exposure; and
9 WHEREAS, the National Association of Insurance Commissioners states that rising claims
10 costs driven primarily by increased frequency of severe storms and rising replacement costs
11 continued to challenge United States property and casualty insurers; and
12 WHEREAS, these increasing prices disproportionally affect small businesses who may be
13 forced to purchase lower limits that do not cover their replacement costs; and
