14 WHEREAS, Georgia Commissioner of Agriculture Tyler Harper and Governor Brian P.
15 Kemp, the University of Georgia College of Agricultural and Environmental Sciences, and
16 the Georgia Forestry Commission announced the preliminary estimate of Hurricane Helene's
17 economic impact on Georgia agriculture is $6.46 billion; and
18 WHEREAS, Georgia Commissioner of Agriculture Tyler Harper stated, "The future is
19 uncertain for thousands of Georgia farmers and farm families who were devastated by
20 Hurricane Helene"; and
21 WHEREAS, increased capacity in Georgia's commercial property and casualty reinsurance
22 market will significantly reduce the overhead costs for all businesses, especially small
23 businesses.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES:
25 (1) Creation of House study committee. There is created the House Study Committee
26 on Reinsurance for Essential Industries.
27 (2) Members and officers.
28 (A) The committee shall be composed of seven members.
29 (B) The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall appoint five members of the
30 House of Representatives who are members of the House Committee on Insurance.
31 (C) The Speaker shall also appoint an additional two nonlegislative members of the
32 committee as follows:
33 (i) The Commissioner of Insurance, or his or her designee; and
34 (ii) The Commissioner of Agriculture, or his or her designee.
35 (D) The Speaker shall also designate a legislative member of the committee as
36 chairperson of the committee.
