37 (3) Powers and duties.
38 (A) The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs, issues, and
39 problems mentioned above and the terms and conditions necessary for public-private
40 partnerships in Georgia's commercial property and casualty reinsurance market, under
41 which the Georgia Department of Insurance will calculate reinsurance payments to
42 issuers participating in Georgia's Reinsurance for Essential Industries Program.
43 (B) The committee shall identify:
44 (i) Ways in which the state can facilitate special risk pools with public-private funds;
45 (ii) The approximate amount of funding necessary for premium reductions for special
46 risk pools;
47 (iii) Criteria to identify essential industries of strategic interest in the state facilitated
48 special risk pools; and
49 (iv) Industries whose premium reductions would be the most beneficial for Georgia's
50 economy.
51 (C) The committee shall recommend any action or legislation which it deems necessary
52 or appropriate.
53 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
54 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
55 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
56 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
57 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
58 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
59 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
60 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
61 or who are state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the
62 committee, but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the
